<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><!DOCTYPE paragraph PUBLIC "-//IFRS//DTD DITA Paragraph//EN" "../../../DocTypes/com.ifrs.doctype/dtd/paragraph.dtd"><paragraph id="IAS28_6" base="F16124135" principles="no"><paranum class="- topic/title paragraph/paranum "/><titlealts><navtitle>6</navtitle></titlealts><prolog><data name="standard_number" value="IAS&#xa0;28"/><data name="paranum" value="6"/></prolog><body><p id="IAS28_P0032">The existence of significant influence by an entity is usually evidenced in one or more of the following ways: </p><ol outputclass="static" id="IAS28_L0002" base="F16124137" type="lower-alpha"><li><li_value>(a)</li_value> <p id="IAS28_P0033" base="F16124138">representation on the board of directors or equivalent governing body of the investee;</p></li><li><li_value>(b)</li_value> <p id="IAS28_P0034" base="F16124140">participation in policy-making processes, including participation in decisions about dividends or other distributions;</p></li><li><li_value>(c)</li_value> <p id="IAS28_P0035" base="F16124144">material transactions between the entity and its investee;</p></li><li><li_value>(d)</li_value> <p id="IAS28_P0036" base="F16124148">interchange of managerial personnel; or</p></li><li><li_value>(e)</li_value> <p id="IAS28_P0037" base="F16124150">provision of essential technical information.</p></li></ol></body></paragraph>